HEADWORD: Effendi
<hw>Ef*fen"di</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>, <ety>[Turk.
<ets>efendi</ets>, fr. Modern Gr. <?/, fr. Gr. <?/ a chief. See
<er>Authentic</er>.]</ety> <def>Master; sir; -- a Turkish title of
respect, applied esp. to a state official or man of learning, as one
learned in the law, but often simply as the courtesy title of a
gentleman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

